{
  "$comment": "Inventory index of every agent-facing `agentos --json` result family and the committed, versioned JSON Schema each maps to (issue #634). This file is the single source of truth the anti-drift contract test `cli/tests/schema_inventory.rs` enforces: it walks `cli/src` for every `impl CliOutput` and cross-checks it against the `results` entries here, so a new result family that lands without a schema fails CI. Each `kind` is either `CliOutput` (auto-discovered from the source) or `builder`/`raw` (a hand-declared free-function or direct-`emit_json` result, the tractable-half scope note mirrored from cli/tests/support/emit_parity.rs). The `version` MUST equal the `/vN` segment of the schema's `$id`.",
  "compatibility_policy": "docs/adr/0074-versioned-json-schemas-for-cli-results.md",
  "discovery": "These schema files are bundled into released `agentos` CLI binaries and printed on demand: `agentos schema-index` emits this index, `agentos schema-index <name>` emits a named schema. In a source checkout they live at cli/schema/.",
